The Open Science Conference 2018, organized by the Leibniz Research Alliance Science 2.0, is dedicated to the Open Science movement and provides a unique forum for researchers, librarians, practitioners, infrastructure providers, and policy makers to discuss and exchange their ideas and experiences. The thematic focus of this year’s conference will be on FAIR principles of research data (i.e. findable, accessible, interoperable, and reusable) and supporting research data infrastructures.


The conference features a lightning talks poster session, a panel discussion on FAIR research data, and a programme of international speakers, including one of LMU Open Science Center’s members: Felix Schönbrodt will talk about “Changing incentive structures to foster the actual sharing rate of open data”.


Registration is open now, with reduced early bird rates until 9th February 2018.

